3 And let us arise, and go up to Beth-el; and I will make there an al- tar unto God, who answered me in the day of my distress, and was with me in the way which I went.
4 And they gave unto Jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings which were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the oak which was by Shechem.
5 And they journeyed: and the ter- ror of God was upon the cities that were round about them, and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob.
