1 This then was the lot of the tribe
of the children of Judah by their families; even to the border of Edom the wilderness of Zin southward was the uttermost part of the south coast.
2 And their south border was from the shore of the salt sea, from the bay that looketh southward:
3 And it went out to the south side to Maaleh-acrabbim, and passed along to Zin, and ascended up on the south side unto Kadesh-barnea, and passed along to Hezron, and went up to Adar, and fetched a com- pass to Karkaa:
4 From thence it passed toward Az- mon, and went out unto the river of Egypt; and the goings out of that coast were at the sea: this shall be your south coast.
